            <bug_when>2013-12-12 10:07:22 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>We use a tool named commitlogreport to extract the commit logs for every developer. Based on that, we write the release notes, which is a tedious task to do. We should improve the generated output for faster processing for writing release notes. Any ideas are welcome!

Here are a few ideas what could be done:
- Parse the [BUG #xxxx] notation to the wiki format we all should use ([[BUG&gt;xxxx]])
- Remove all commits having only &quot;minor&quot; as message</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>34627</commentid>
            <who name="Thomas Herchenroeder">thron7</who>
            <bug_when>2013-12-12 10:20:48 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>One idea that came up before is to use a dedicated commit tag instead of &quot;BUG&quot;, 
e.g.

  [RELNOTE #xxx] &lt;... message for the release notes ...&gt;

or &quot;RELEASE&quot; or something.

This would make it trivial to extract the relevant comments, and developers had 
full control over which comments go into the extract. This could even work 
without bug numbers.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
